The Americas
------------
[4] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Wed 23 Nov 2011
Source: iNews880AM [edited]
http://www.inews880.com/Channels/Reg/LocalNews/story.aspx?ID=1576429


It turns out some suspected cases of measles were just that,
suspected, and not the real infection. As iNews880 reported last week,
Alberta Health Services (AHS) were awaiting test results of potential
secondary cases of measles, after one person tested positive for it.
Alberta Health Services confirms test results from all 3 [suspected]
cases have come back negative.

One person did test positive for measles, prompting AHS to send out a
warning to those who may have come into contact with that person at
Manulife Place, between 7am-9pm, 1-3 Nov 2011; the Synergy Fall Social
Event at Sutton Place Hotel, 3 Nov 2011, 5pm-9pm; or the emergency
room at University Hospital, 8 Nov 2011, 7:30pm and 9 Nov 2011,
4:30am.

Measles is highly contagious and potentially-deadly if you haven't
been immunized against it.

Alberta Health Services is still advising anyone showing such symptoms
as a fever, cough, runny nose, red eyes, and blotchy rash to get in
touch with Health Link Alberta, 780-408-LINK (5465) in Edmonton, or
toll-free, 1-866-408-LINK.

[Byline: Brenton Driedger]

