[5] Ecuador (Chimborazo)
Date Thu 24 Nov 2011
Source: Diario Los Andes [in Spanish, trans Mod.JG, abbreviated &
edited]
http://www.diariolosandes.com.ec/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1017:salud-confirmo-tres-casos-de-sarampion-&catid=59:portada&Itemid=157


109 cases of [suspected] measles have been reported in the province of
Chimborazo, Of these, 106 were negative and 3 positive according to a
press release from the head of Epidemiology, Bureau of Health of
Chimborazo. The results for 7 other cases are pending.

To date, 89 percent of children 6 months to one year old and 84
percent of children one to 4 years of age have been registered as
vaccinated against measles, mumps and rubella virus infection.

Meanwhile, the health authorities are continuing to vaccinate children
between 5 and 15 years of age. The confirmed cases are a child 5 years
old, a 3-year-old girl, and a 14-year-old boy. The 3 had not been
vaccinated against measles virus infection because of opposition from
their parents.

