[7] Australia (ACT)
Date: Fri 25 Nov 2011
From: The Canberra Times [abbreviated, edited]
http://www.canberratimes.com.au/news/local/news/general/father-fears-more-exposed-to-measles-outbreak/2370322.aspx


A parent's 15-year-old daughter seems to be over the worst of a
suspected case of measles but is worried about how many other people
she may have inadvertently exposed to the disease. ''She still has a
really nasty cough, and her body is still covered in a rash, but it's
far less aggressive than it was 2 or 3 days ago."

The girl -- who has not been vaccinated against measles -- is a Year 9
student at the Orana Steiner School in Weston, where 4 of her
classmates have been diagnosed with the illness, and one has been
admitted to hospital. More cases are expected to be diagnosed, and
health authorities have the task of trying to contact everybody who
may have been in close contact with sufferers, including people who
may have sat next to them in medical waiting rooms.

The family was also concerned about the girl's 8-week-old daughter,
although the fact the baby was being breastfed by her vaccinated
mother was likely to offer strong protection against measles.

[Byline: Peter Jean]

